#: src/0066-better-temporary-lifetimes.md:37
msgid "Detailed design"
msgstr ""

#: src/0066-better-temporary-lifetimes.md:39
msgid ""
"When a reference to a temporary is passed to a function (either as a regular "
"argument or as the `self` argument of a method), and the function returns a "
"value with the same lifetime as the temporary reference, the lifetime of the "
"temporary should be extended the same way it would if the function was not "
"invoked."
msgstr ""

#: src/0066-better-temporary-lifetimes.md:45
msgid ""
"For example, `~[T].as_slice()` takes `&'a self` and returns `&'a [T]`. "
"Calling `as_slice()` on a temporary of type `~[T]` will implicitly take a "
"reference `&'a ~[T]` and return a value `&'a [T]` This return value should "
"be considered to extend the lifetime of the `~[T]` temporary just as taking "
"an explicit reference (and skipping the method call) would."
msgstr ""

